    "industrial_process_notes": "First synthesized in 1930 by Hans Fikentscher and Claus Heuck at IG Farben (Ludwigshafen); early research stalled because PAN did not dissolve in any industrial solvent of the time until Herbert Rein identified suitable solvents in 1938, enabling fiber production. DuPont ran the first mass production of PAN fiber in 1946 (Orlon). The carbon-fiber precursor route involves thermal oxidative stabilization at ~230°C in air, then carbonization above 1000°C in an inert atmosphere.",
